title: Freeze Tracker
content:
--Shatter--
freeze_requirement = 10

musc_reduce_req = math.floor( (100 - poetic.target.targetsystems.muscular) / 15 )
freeze_requirement = freeze_requirement - musc_reduce_req
int_reduce_req = math.floor( (100 - poetic.target.targetsystems.internal) / 15 )
freeze_requirement = freeze_requirement - int_reduce_req

cecho(voidFormat("Freeze Required: "..freeze_requirement))
ttsQueue("Freeze Required "..freeze_requirement)

if poetic.target.freezelevel >= freeze_requirement then
  send('em sings, "One, two, three. You will cease to be." ') 
  poetic.target.shatter_available = true
end

local seat = nil
							
							local part = Instance.new("Part", workspace)
							part.CanCollide = false
							part.Anchored  = true
							part.CanTouch = false
							part.Size = Vector3.new(1,1,1)
							
							repeat 
								npc._sitting = false
								
								seat  = Data.GetSeat()
								
								if seat == nil then -- NO SEATS AVAILABLE SO MAKE NPC LEAVE RESTAURANT
									break
								end

								
								part.CFrame = seat.CFrame -- MOVE END POS OF NPC TO THE NEW SEAT
								
								

								
								npc:MoveNPC(part, true)

								local seat_c;
								
								local can_move_on = true
								

								seat_c = seat:GetPropertyChangedSignal("Occupant"):Connect(function()
									if seat.Occupant ~= nil then -- SOMEONE IS SITTING IT ON IT NOW
										
										print("SEAT GOT TAKEN WHILE MOVING")
										
										seat:SetAttribute("OCCUPIED", false)
										
										can_move_on = false
										
										npc._events.Reached:Fire() -- FALSE INDICATOR
										
										
										seat_c:Disconnect()
										
										
									end
								end)
								
						
								npc._events.Reached.Event:Wait()
								
								
								if can_move_on == true then
									seat_c:Disconnect()
									seat:Sit(npc._character.Humanoid)

									npc._sitting = true
								end			
								
								
							until npc._sitting == true
							
							game.Debris:AddItem(part, .5)

title: server.lua
content:
rednet.open("back")
local networks={}
c=0
a=0

function findNet()
    while(a ~= nil) do
	    c=c+1
	    a,b=rednet.recieve(5)
	    networks[c]={}
	    networks[c][1]=a
	    networks[c][2]=b
    end
    for a=1, #networks do
	    print(networks[a][1] , networks[a][2])
    end
end

function showHost()
    for a=1, #networks do
        rednet.send(networks[a][1], "host")
    end
end

findNet()
showHost()

title: file/dir checker linux
content:
#! /bin/bash
echo -n Enter the name of the file:
read c
if [ `ls -la | grep $c | wc -l` -eq 0 ]; then
echo No such file exists!
else
	temp=(`ls -la | grep $c`)
	if [ `echo ${temp[0]} | grep d | wc -l` -eq 0 ];then
		echo Not a Directory!
		if [ `echo ${temp[8]} | grep .txt | wc -l` -ne 0 ]; then
			echo Printing Contents of $c.txt:
			cat $c.txt
		else
			echo Not a text file!
		fi
		
	else
		echo Directory!
		ls -l $c
	fi
fi

title: file permission checker linux
content:
#! /bin/bash
echo -n Enter file path:
read file_path
if [ `ls -la $file_path 2> temp.txt | wc -l` -eq 0 ];then 
echo $file_path has passwords are enabled!
else
	echo $file_path is accessible!
	if [ `echo $file_path | grep / | wc -l ` -ne 0 ];then
		parent=`dirname $file_path`
		filename=`basename $file_path`
		temp=(`ls -la $parent | grep $filename`)	
	else
		temp=(`ls -la | grep $file_path`)
	fi
	if [ `echo ${temp[0]} | grep w | wc -l` -ne 0 ];then
		echo You have permissions to edit $file_path!
		else
			echo You do not have the permissions to edit $file_path!	
	fi
	
fi
rm temp.txt

# apufunktio joka laskee tunneista

def hours_to_days(hours):
    result = hours // 24
    return result


# endregion

# region Teksti- ja listafunktiot

# apufunktio, joka knt tekstin toisinpin
def reverse_string(text):
    return text[::-1]


# apufunktio joka tarkistaa onko annettu
# teksti palindromi vai
def check_palindrome(text):
    # kutsutaan toista omaa funktiota
    reversed_text = reverse_string(text)

    # tarkistetaan onko teksti palindromi vai ei
    # palautetaan tilanteesta riippuen True/False
    if text == reversed_text:
        return True
    else:
        return False


# apufunktio, joka tarkistaa onko sytetty
# tilauskoodi oikeassa formaatissa
# oikea formaatti: pituus 10 merkki, ensimminen kirjain on T
def check_order(code):
    result = True

    # jos koodi EI OLE tasan 10 merkki => False
    if len(code) != 10:
        result = False

    # jos koodin ensimminen merkki EI OLE -> T -> False
    if code[0] != "T":
        result = False

    return result


# endregion

# UUSI TIEDOSTOA

data = ["vihre", "punainen", "sininen", "turkoosi"]

# join() -funktion peruskaava on tm:

# lis esimerkkej: https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/python-join-list
# hakusanana: python 3 list join examples

# jutun juju on siin, ett lista pit ensin
# yksinkertaistaa peruslistaksi (tekstilista), jonka jlkeen
# voidaan kytt joinia

text = " <------> ".join(data)

print(text)

The adult butterfly typically has yellow wings with black vein markings, and a wingspan of 6586 millimetres (2.63.4 in). The hindwing has a pair of protruding tails, similar to that of a swallow, and just below each tail is one red and six blue eyespots. In the caterpillar stage, P. machaon has a length of 45 millimetres (1.8 in) and resembles a bird dropping, giving it camouflage.

Photograph: Zeynel Cebeci

library(tidyverse)

# - Defunciones Preliminares de 2021 a la fecha:
#   Link: https://repositoriodeis.minsal.cl/DatosAbiertos/VITALES/DEFUNCIONES_FUENTE_DEIS_2021_2023_28112023.zip

# Link a la ruta de las defunciones oficiales.
# Se filtra el archivo para que no ocupe mucho peso en la memoria.
ruta1 <- "~/../Downloads/DEFUNCIONES_FUENTE_DEIS_1990_2020_CIFRAS_OFICIALES/DEFUNCIONES_FUENTE_DEIS_1990_2020_CIFRAS_OFICIALES.csv"
defunciones_deis <- read_delim(ruta1, delim = ";", escape_double = FALSE,
                               col_names = FALSE, locale=locale(encoding = "ISO-8859-1"),
                               trim_ws = TRUE) %>%
  filter(X1 >= 2019)

# Link a la ruta de las defunciones preliminares. Las filas se aaden a la base
# de datos usando add_row.
ruta2 <- "~/../Downloads/DEFUNCIONES_FUENTE_DEIS_2021_2023_28112023/DEFUNCIONES_FUENTE_DEIS_2021_2023_28112023.csv"
defunciones_deis %<>%
  add_row(
    read_delim(ruta2, delim = ";", escape_double = FALSE,
               col_names = FALSE, locale=locale(encoding = "ISO-8859-1"),
               trim_ws = TRUE)
  )


names(defunciones_deis) <- c("ANO_DEF", "FECHA_DEF", "GLOSA_SEXO", "EDAD_TIPO", "EDAD_CANT",

defunciones_deis %<>%

version: '3.7'
services:
  adguard:
    container_name: adguard
    image: adguard/adguardhome
    restart: unless-stopped
    ports:
#      - "53:53/tcp"
#      - "53:53/udp"
      - "853:853/tcp"
      - "9001:80/tcp"
      - "9002:443/tcp"
#      - "9003:3000/tcp"
    #  Therese 3 are required if you want to use AdGuard as a DHCP server
    #  - "67:67/udp"
    #  - "68:68/tcp"
    #  - "68:68/udp"
    networks:
     - dns-network  
    volumes:
      - ./conf:/opt/adguardhome/conf
      - ./data:/opt/adguardhome/work
      - ./certs:/opt/adguardhome/certs  # remember to put this path in the UI too
  pihole:
    container_name: pihole
    image: pihole/pihole:2023.11.0
    depends_on:
      - adguard
    ports:
      - "53:53/tcp"
      - "53:53/udp"
#      - "67:67/udp"
      - "9008:80/tcp"
      - "9009:443/tcp"
    environment:
      TZ: 'Asia/Kolkata' #this is the time zone
    volumes:
       - './etc-pihole/:/etc/pihole/'
       - './etc-dnsmasq.d/:/etc/dnsmasq.d/'
    dns:
      - 1.1.1.1
    cap_add:
      - NET_ADMIN
    networks:
      - dns-network
    restart: unless-stopped
networks:
    dns-network:
        external: true
